# Hosting a [[mirror|run a mirror]]

Given that Libravatar is a community project without a big corporate sponsor, we need help serving images.

If you can spare a bit of disk space and bandwidth, please [get in touch](mailto:mirrors@libravatar.org), we would love your help in building a world-wide mirror network.

# Advocacy

If you don't fit into of the other categories, you are still more than welcome to come and hang out on our [IRC channel](irc://chat.freenode.net/%23libravatar) ([web interface](http://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=libravatar)).

And of course, feel free to submit feature requests for your favourite applications to add support for Libravatar.
